          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I joined TBISC in 2017. At that time I just finished YEAR 9 back in Bahrain and when we came to India to check for admissions most schools wouldn't want to take me in since I came in the middle of IGCSE. But then I found TBISC and they had admissions open throughout the year making it flexible for international students to join.\n\nI came in with no expectations but once I met the students, teachers and faculty I instantly felt like I was back home in Bahrain. Lots of students from different countries, cultures and backgrounds. People might think\" Oh, it's a small school or it has few students\"' but it's an advantage since you get individual attention from teachers.\n\nMy grades have improved drastically after coming here and I acquired a lot of new skills as well. TBISC was a great exposure and I would like to thank TBISC for making it a memorable one.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "The British International School - Neelankarai"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Sanjay Baskaran"
          },
          "datePublished": "2020-02-18",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I moved to Chennai from the UK in 2016. The most important qualities in a school which I looked for is a diverse culture, with many students from all corners of the world, a calm and easy atmosphere to excel in your academics and a supportive group of faculty, who are willing to push and support you in maximizing your core-capabilities.  TBISC has definitely ticked all of the above boxes and it has been a pleasure for me to be a part of this institute. 2016-2020, the moments i have spent here has left a firm imprint, which will have a lasting effect. The education and lessons gained here has nurtured a better me, ready for the foreseeable future",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "The British International School - Neelankarai"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Saratha Natarajan"
          },
          "datePublished": "2020-01-20",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I have been in this school for more than 3 years working as Mathematics, ICT Teacher handling Year 9 to A Levels. We always have two teachers for each subjects. We have well qualified teachers for Physics, Chemistry & Biology. Edexcel is the best curriculum compared to other International curriculum in the world. TBISC provides customized environment to meet each student requirement and ensuring the adequate support to students. We are offering iPrimary and iSecondary curriculam for Year 6 and Year 8 grades which will help them to score higher grades in IGCSE , AS & A Levels. I strongly recommend this school for Edexcel. Every day is a learning experience. I am enjoying every day !",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "The British International School - Neelankarai"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Previna Sharon"
          },
          "datePublished": "2019-08-19",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I have close association with this school for the past 4+ years. This school is well organized in their management, curriculum and teaching. The students learn a lot with pleasure and not with pressure. Those who study in TBISC will definitely show overall progress. Unique way of providing opportunity to expose themselves more on various activities like MUN, seminar, summit, field trips and study trips helps in buildings their confidence. It's worth paying! I wish I was a student of this school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "The British International School - Neelankarai"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "T P Rajmanohar"
          },
          "datePublished": "2018-11-24",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I  joined  TBISC in 2010  and have add an enjoyable  eight years working here.  The school is very strong on academics  and many of my students have got 100% in the board examinations. It  has good sports activities like table tennis, chess, shuttle badminton  etc. In most of these sports the school has qualified coaches.  In terms of extracurricular activities  there is a MUN club, aeromodelling club, dance, music, art and craft  and yoga  and silambam. Hence the student gets a very good balanced education.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
